	<pb n="0001" facs="liv_002034_0001"/><!--pb/@n='5r'-->
<lb/><p rend="right"><placeName><choice><sic>Burn Bank</sic><corr>Burnbank</corr></choice> Road</placeName></p>
<lb/><p rend="right"><placeName>Hamilton</placeName> 2<hi rend="underline"><hi rend="sup">d</hi></hi> Aug.</p>
<lb/><p rend="right">1864 </p>
<lb/><p>My Dear <persName>M<hi rend="sup"><hi rend="underline">r</hi></hi> Murray</persName></p>
<lb/><p>As you kindly 
<lb/>promised to take 
<lb/>notice of any 
<lb/>quiet cottage that 
<lb/>might suit me 
<lb/>I may mention 
<lb/>that I have resolved 
<lb/>to take my daughter 
<lb/>who is now 
<lb/>woman grown 
<lb/>with me to keep it

	<pb n="0002" facs="liv_002034_0002"/><!--pb/@n='5v'-->
<lb/>and as she will 
<lb/>require a music 
<lb/>master if the 
<lb/>cottage were where 
<lb/>one would call 
<lb/>occasionally it 
<lb/>would be an 
<lb/>advantage. I am 
<lb/>keeping myself 
<lb/>free from all 
<lb/>public appearances 
<lb/>as they call 
<lb/>lecturing except 
<lb/>the British Association<reg>.</reg>

	<pb n="0003" facs="liv_002034_0003"/><!--pb/@n='6r'-->
<lb/>A second son who 
<lb/>lost his health 
<lb/>at a abomin<add place="above">a</add>bly 
<lb/>drained Scotch 
<lb/>school will 
<lb/>accompany 
<lb/>me to <placeName>England</placeName> &amp; 
<lb/>I think with son 
<lb/>&amp; daughter I may 
<lb/>get on comfortably<reg>.</reg>
<lb/>My Scotch friends 
<lb/>think that by 
<lb/>giving the public 
<lb/>information on 
<lb/>the actual working 
<lb/>of the slave trade 

	<pb n="0004" facs="liv_002034_0004"/><!--pb/@n='6v'-->
<lb/>and the rock on which 
<lb/>the mission split 
<lb/>I may do good. It 
<lb/>will be difficult to 
<lb/>do the last without 
<lb/>offence - but we can 
<lb/>try to do it in a kindly spirit. <choice><reg>T</reg><orig>t</orig></choice>he 
<lb/>bishop of <placeName>Oxford</placeName>
<lb/>is anxious to see 
<lb/>me. I conjecture 
<lb/>on the Mission 
<lb/>subject. </p>
<lb/><p><persName>D<hi rend="underline"><hi rend="sup">r</hi></hi> Meller</persName> has a brother 
<lb/>in a house agent's 
<lb/>employment. Would it 
<lb/>be well to employ this 
<lb/><addSpan spanTo="#p5r-01" place="marginleft"><!--addSpan/@place='left margin of fol. 5r'--></addSpan>man if you see nothing. He is in <del type="strikethrough"><placeName>Bond St</placeName></del>
<lb/><placeName>Old Broad St. City.</placeName> With kind regards to <persName>M<hi rend="sup"><hi rend="underline">rs</hi></hi>
<lb/>Murray</persName><reg>.</reg> I am &amp;c <persName>David Livingstone</persName></p><anchor xml:id="p5r-01"/>
			
